The paper deals with combinatorial triangulations, which are a fundamental topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of edge flips to transform triangulations is a common technique in computational geometry and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves analyzing the flip graph, which is a graph-theoretic object, making it relevant to graph theory (cs.GT). The authors also mention the use of algorithms to perform the edge flips, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's results have implications for the efficiency of certain algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity and cryptography (cs.SI).
